  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nYou're designing a school planner app that tracks how much time a student spends studying two subjects. The app calculates total study time and compares the two.\r\n\r\n1. Two variables are already set up: `math_minutes` and `science_minutes`\r\n\r\n2. Use math operations to:\r\n\r\n   * Add the study times together\r\n   \r\n   * Subtract one from the other\r\n   \r\n   * Multiply the times\r\n   \r\n   * Divide one by the other\r\n\r\n3. Use `print()` statements to show each result.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nYou can use `+`, `-`, `*`, and `/` to do math with numbers in Python — just like on a calculator!",
